<p><b>Steven Weinberg</b> (born <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1933-05-03"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="05-03"><a href="/wiki/May_3" title="May 3">May 3</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1933" title="1933">1933</a></span>) is an <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">American</a> <a href="/wiki/Physicist" title="Physicist">physicist</a> and <a href="/wiki/Nobel_Prize_in_Physics" title="Nobel Prize in Physics">Nobel laureate in Physics</a> for his contributions with <a href="/wiki/Abdus_Salam" title="Abdus Salam">Abdus Salam</a> and <a href="/wiki/Sheldon_Lee_Glashow" title="Sheldon Lee Glashow">Sheldon Glashow</a> to the <a href="/wiki/Electroweak_interaction" title="Electroweak interaction">unification</a> of the <a href="/wiki/Weak_force" title="Weak force" class="mw-redirect">weak force</a> and <a href="/wiki/Electromagnetism" title="Electromagnetism">electromagnetic</a> interaction between elementary particles.</p>
